The API for this method has a little bit of caveat emptor: it doesn't play nicely with leap years.

Let's say the following are true:
* {{TimeZone.getDefault()}} returns +0 GMT.
* {{new Date()}} returns the 31st of December.

If you were to call the following code: {code}
final Map dateMap = new LinkedHashMap();
DataUtils.normaliseDateRangeCount(dateMap, 730, Year.class, TimeZone.getDefault()){code}

This is a sort of obtuse way of asking "How many years were there between now and 730 days ago?"

Most years, the answer will be three. However, on the 31st of December of a leap year, the answer will be 2.

Mathematically speaking, the method is correct. Semantically speaking, though, is this a bug in the design of the API?

