When accessing GMail via IMAP, Plain-Text attachments are not considered as attachments.
The identified root cause is that the Attachment have their Content-Disposition in UPPERCASE, when the MailUtils.getBodyFromMultipart() is executed.

{code:java}
if (!Part.ATTACHMENT.equals(part.getDisposition()) && contentType != null)
 {
  try {
   String content = extractTextFromPart(part);
   if (content != null) {
     appendMultipartText(content, sb);
  }
...
{code}

The effect is that some attachments are loaded as Description as soon as they do have a Plain Text Content-Type.

Tests have been done with JIRA 5.1.8 (including mail-1.4.5) with embedded Tomcat.

I did not have identified why it is in uppercase ...
The Test Mails has been created from Thunderbird connected in IMAP and also from GMail WebUI.
When I request to see the Message (Ctrl+U) from Thunderbird, the Content-Disposition is correctly displayed in Lowercase in both cases.

I have follow in Debug until com.sun.mail.imap.protocol.BODYSTRUCTURE where the FetchResponse returns :
{code}* 1 FETCH (BODYSTRUCTURE (("TEXT" "PLAIN" ("CHARSET" "ISO-8859-1" "FORMAT" "flowed") NIL NIL "7BIT" 11 1 NIL NIL NIL)("TEXT" "PLAIN" ("CHARSET" "windows-1252" "NAME" "README2.txt") NIL NIL "BASE64" 0 0 NIL ("ATTACHMENT" ("FILENAME" "README2.txt")) NIL)("TEXT" "PLAIN" ("CHARSET" "windows-1252" "NAME" "README.txt") NIL NIL "BASE64" 6428 86 NIL ("ATTACHMENT" ("FILENAME" "README.txt")) NIL) "MIXED" ("BOUNDARY" "------------050602000209030707010209") NIL NIL))
{code}

Simple solution to generalize : 
{code:java}!Part.ATTACHMENT.equalsIgnoreCase(part.getDisposition()){code}

Same think in *isAttachment(BodyPart)* method :
{code:java}
    private static boolean isAttachment(BodyPart part)
            throws MessagingException
    {
        return Part.ATTACHMENT.equalsIgnoreCase(part.getDisposition()) || Part.INLINE.equalsIgnoreCase(part.getDisposition())
				|| (part.getDisposition() == null && part.getFileName() != null);
    }
{code}

Vincent

